## Notes & Warnings

- This is a low-priority housekeeping task but should be done early to establish clean development practices
- Do not exclude legitimate code directories (backend/, frontend/, scripts/ should NOT be ignored)
- Only ignore generated/temporary files and build artifacts
- The .gitignore file itself should be committed to Git (not ignored)
- Use forward slashes (/) for directory patterns to ensure cross-platform compatibility
- Comments in gitignore start with # and are for documentation
- Can verify ignoring is working by checking git index: `git ls-files --others --ignored --exclude-standard`
